      "comment_id" : 51758479,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "If you rely on JSR-* annotations only, sure, you <i>can</i> replace you DI framework. But will you? Once you&#39;ve started using spring, chances are you&#39;ve used a lot more of it than just DI. You won&#39;t just make a change; and even if you do, it&#39;s not a few search &amp; replaces that is going to make or break the move. On the other hand, Spring&#39;s own annotations offer you a lot more functionality. Mastering a good framework will give you more than hardly using many."
