      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1504797944,
      "post_id" : 17695848,
      "comment_id" : 79162571,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "It&#39;s not a must to run Spring in a JEE container, you can also use it in a servlet/JSP container like Tomcat and still have the JSR-330 support. Spring is a separate DI container, it does not &quot;interchange&quot; CDI beans with the host JEE server if its that what you mean. You may either use CDI in a JEE container, or Spring beans - but you can&#39;t use both (out of the box)."
    } ],
